From 98747aa3ce5e483bc2c8bdcdc31d3f0a800fc35c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Joakim Bech <Joakim.Bech@analog.com>
Date: Fri, 19 Dec 2025 14:01:06 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] Add gitignore rule for preprocessed assembly files

GCC preprocessing generates lowercase .s files from uppercase .S source files
in CMSIS device directories. These are intermediate build artifacts that should
not be tracked in the repository.

- Added pattern: Libraries/CMSIS/Device/**/Source/**/*.s
- Prevents clutter from preprocessed assembly artifacts

Signed-off-by: Joakim Bech <Joakim.Bech@analog.com>
---
 .gitignore | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/.gitignore b/.gitignore
index 3beee389c7..34ed5d94ca 100644
--- a/.gitignore
+++ b/.gitignore
@@ -6,6 +6,7 @@ Examples/*/*/*/buildrv
 .vscode/settings.json
 Libraries/PeriphDrivers/Documentation/MAX*
 Libraries/PeriphDrivers/bin
+Libraries/CMSIS/Device/**/Source/**/*.s
 Documentation/Libraries
 Documentation/res
 Examples/MAX78000/PowerTest
-- 
